《'''沃洛克阴谋'''》（{{lang-en|The Volokh Conspiracy}}<ref name="LindRankin2012">{{cite book|author1=Nancy S. Lind|author2=Erik T. Rankin|title=First Amendment Rights: An Encyclopedia [2 volumes]: An Encyclopedia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4K0CWvR2FNEC&pg=PA406|date=21 November 2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-61069-213-7|pages=406–|access-date=2020-07-13|archive-date=2020-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200713203039/https://books.google.com/books?id=4K0CWvR2FNEC&pg=PA406|dead-url=no}}</ref>）是一个由[[加州大学洛杉矶分校法学院|加州大学洛杉矶分校法学院]]教授[[尤金·沃洛克|尤金·沃洛克]]（Eugene Volokh）<ref name="Davis2014">{{cite book|author=Richard Davis|title=Covering the United States Supreme Court in the Digital Age|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SC4DBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA185|date=11 August 2014|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-05245-1|pages=185–|access-date=2020-07-13|archive-date=2020-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809173246/https://books.google.com/books?id=SC4DBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA185|dead-url=no}}</ref>于2002年创建的[[法律|法律]][[博客|博客]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lamag.com/citythinkblog/right-side-law-eugene-volokhs-global-influence/|title=Right Side of the Law: Eugene Volokh’s Global Influence|date=April 1, 2015|website=Los Angeles Magazine|author=Preston Lerner|accessdate=2020-07-13|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308054739/https://www.lamag.com/citythinkblog/right-side-law-eugene-volokhs-global-influence/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。它从[[意识形态|意识形态]]的取向出发，关注[[法律|法律]]和[[政治|政治]]议题<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=2LW1-5E7jsQC&pg=PA185 Cass R. Sunstein, Infotopia: how many minds produce knowledge] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2LW1-5E7jsQC&pg=PA185 |date=20200930220900 }}, Oxford Univ Press (2006); {{ISBN|978-0-19-518928-5}}.</ref>。该网站称自己的立场「一般来说是[[美国式自由意志主义|美国式自由意志主义]]、[[保守主义|保守主义]]、[[中间主义|中间主义]]，或者是它们的混合」<ref>Julia Bergman.{{cite web|url=https://www.theday.com/article/20150413/NWS01/150419742|title=Conn College professor's Facebook post gets attention from Washington Post blog|work=theday.com|date=2015-04-13|access-date=2020-07-13|archive-date=2020-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200713104648/https://www.theday.com/article/20150413/NWS01/150419742|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

该博客的名称是对[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]在1998年声称有一个“[[巨大右翼阴谋|巨大右翼阴谋]]”（"vast right-wing conspiracy"）的戏称，她认为这个[[阴谋|阴谋]]正在迫害她和她的丈夫[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]][[总统|总统]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tabletmag.com/sections/news/articles/the-volokh-conspiracy|title=The Volokh Conspiracy Is Out To Get You—And Everyone in America|date=2014-04-03|website=Tablet Magazine|author=Yair Rosenberg|accessdate=2020-07-13|archive-date=2021-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216083446/https://www.tabletmag.com/sections/news/articles/the-volokh-conspiracy|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2007年，《[[高校情报|高校情报]]》（Inside Higher Ed）的安迪·盖斯写道，它是“美国阅读量最大的法律博客之一”，它 “在该领域的影响力和直接影响，可能超过大多数法律评论刊物”<ref name="Guess">Andy Guess. [http://www.insidehighered.com/news/2008/05/09/blogs "Blogs and Wikis and 3D, Oh My!"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.insidehighered.com/news/2008/05/09/blogs |date=20210227093103 }}. Inside Higher Ed. 2008-05-09.</ref>。

《[[大西洋_(杂志)|大西洋杂志]]》[[亚当·泰霍尔茨|亚当·泰霍尔茨]]（Adam Teicholz）称，相较于其它博客，《沃洛克阴谋》在影响[[美国人|美国人]]反对《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|患者保护与平价医疗法案]]》这方面发挥了重要作用<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2012/03/did-bloggers-kill-the-health-care-mandate/255182/|title=Did Bloggers Kill the Health Care Mandate?|first=Adam|last=Teicholz|work=theatlantic.com|date=March 28, 2012|accessdate=December 26, 2016|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314181418/https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2012/03/did-bloggers-kill-the-health-care-mandate/255182/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年，《沃洛克阴谋》被《[[美国律师协会期刊|美国律师协会期刊]]》纳入“法律博客名人堂”（"Blawg 100 Hall of Fame"）<ref name="paywall">{{cite web|url=http://www.abajournal.com/news/article/around_the_blawgosphere_volokh_dynamic_pricing_ponzi_schemes_snow_on_cars|title=Volokh Conspiracy blog now subject to Washington Post's paywall Can lawyers use dynamic pricing?|publisher=ABA Journal|date=January 24, 2014|author=Mui, Sarah|access-date=2020-07-13|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111232524/https://www.abajournal.com/news/article/around_the_blawgosphere_volokh_dynamic_pricing_ponzi_schemes_snow_on_cars/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2014年1月，《沃洛克阴谋》网站迁移至《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》，同年6月采用[[付费墙|付费墙]]（paywall）模式<ref name="paywall"/>。不过，该博客保留了其对内容的完全编辑控制权<ref>{{cite web|author=Eugene Volokh|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/volokh-conspiracy/wp/2014/01/21/in-brazil-you-can-always-find-the-amazon-in-america-the-amazon-finds-you-2|title=In Brazil, you can always find the Amazon – in America, the Amazon finds you|work=washingtonpost.com|date=January 21, 2014|accessdate=December 26, 2016|archive-date=2021-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119071303/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/volokh-conspiracy/wp/2014/01/21/in-brazil-you-can-always-find-the-amazon-in-america-the-amazon-finds-you-2/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2017年，它又从《华盛顿邮报》迁移到《[[理性_(杂志)|理性杂志]]》，沃洛克称这样做是为了自由访问和自由编辑，以便于在引用的材料中加入未经编辑的[[脏话|脏话]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Volokh |first=Eugene |title=Our Move to (Paywall-free! |url=http://reason.com/volokh/2017/12/13/weve-moved-to-reason |access-date=2017年12月14日 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20171213141527/https://reason.com/volokh/2017/12/13/weve-moved-to-reason |archive-date=2017年12月13日 |url-status=
